  "tips": [
    {
      "type": "lead",
      "text": "Long sentences are the stuff of contracts, reports, and scholarship. A reader trusts you to hold the thread; so must your hands."
    },
    {
      "type": "drop",
      "text": "A clause set off by 'which' is a side road. Mind the rhythm there so you rejoin the main sentence without losing the thought."
    },
    {
      "type": "exercise",
      "target": "Although the meeting was scheduled for ten in the morning, several team members, including the director and",
      "finger": "purple",
      "hint": "Complex sentence flow"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "Don't snatch at the comma, and don't stop for it. Let it pass under your hands at the same even speed as the rest."
    },
    {
      "type": "exercise",
      "target": "the project lead, did not arrive until almost half past, which delayed the agenda by nearly forty-five minutes.",
      "finger": "purple",
