  "character_tips": {
    "anna": "A long sentence tests whether you can hold your focus to the end. Don't fade at the midpoint; carry it through. - Eleanor Hayes, editor",
    "maxim": "Legal and academic writing lives at this length. Learn to sustain it and little will daunt you. - Eleanor Hayes, editor",
    "knopych": "This one runs on. Pace yourself like a long shift, even and unhurried, and you will reach the full stop with something left. - Eleanor Hayes, editor",
    "klavochka": "Think of it as a long phrase of music, held steady from first note to last. - Eleanor Hayes, editor"
